<task id="task-3729" class="- topic/topic task/task "><title class="- topic/title ">Enable TestOps - Jira integration in <ph conkeyref="name-variables/katalon-testops" class="- topic/ph "/></title><taskbody class="- topic/body task/taskbody "><context class="- topic/section task/context ">You can configure TestOps - Jira integration in <ph conkeyref="name-variables/katalon-testops" class="- topic/ph "/>. This integration allows you to:<ul class="- topic/ul "><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Link Jira requirements and Jira defects.</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Link test runs to populated Jira releases.</p></li></ul></context><steps class="- topic/ol task/steps "><step class="- topic/li task/step "><cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Sign in to <xref format="html" href="https://testops.katalon.io/login" scope="external" class="- topic/xref ">Katalon TestOps</xref> and go to your project.</cmd><stepresult class="- topic/itemgroup task/stepresult ">The project <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Dashboard</uicontrol> page appears.</stepresult></step><step class="- topic/li task/step "><cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Select <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Configuration</uicontrol> &gt; <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Integration</uicontrol>.</cmd><stepresult class="- topic/itemgroup task/stepresult ">The <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Integrations</uicontrol> page appears. There is a dropdown menu on the page for a full list of integration options.</stepresult></step><step class="- topic/li task/step "><cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Select <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Jira</uicontrol> in the dropdown menu.</cmd><stepresult class="- topic/itemgroup task/stepresult ">The Jira page appears as below.<p class="- topic/p "><image href="Image/kt-jira-integration.png" class="- topic/image "><alt class="- topic/alt ">Select Jira integration in TestOps</alt></image></p></stepresult></step><step class="- topic/li task/step "><cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Enter Jira URL, Username, and Password.</cmd><info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info "><p class="- topic/p ">For Jira Cloud:</p><ul class="- topic/ul "><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Jira URL must be in the form of <codeph class="+ topic/ph pr-d/codeph ">https://&lt;site_name&gt;.atlassian.net</codeph>.</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">In the <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Username</uicontrol> section, enter the email address you have registered for your Jira Cloud account.</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">In the <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Password</uicontrol> section, enter an Atlassian Cloud's API token. See instructions for API tokens in the Atlassian document: <xref format="html" href="https://confluence.atlassian.com/cloud/api-tokens-938839638.html" scope="external" class="- topic/xref ">API tokens</xref>.</p></li></ul><p class="- topic/p ">For Jira Server:</p><ul class="- topic/ul "><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Jira URL must be in the form of <codeph class="+ topic/ph pr-d/codeph ">http(s)://domain</codeph>, without any trailing parts. For example, <codeph class="+ topic/ph pr-d/codeph ">/secure</codeph>.</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">In the <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Username</uicontrol> section, enter your Username instead of your email address.</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">In the <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Password</uicontrol> section, enter your Password.</p></li></ul></info></step><step class="- topic/li task/step "><cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Click <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Test Connection</uicontrol> to see if the connection is successful. </cmd></step><step class="- topic/li task/step "><cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Click <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Save</uicontrol>.</cmd></step></steps><result class="- topic/section task/result ">You have successfully enabled TestOps - Jira integration in <ph conkeyref="name-variables/katalon-testops" class="- topic/ph "/>. You can now link test cases to Jira requirements, Jira defects or link test runs to Jira releases.</result></taskbody></task>